# Direct-Syntax Control Flow

Exercises v1.8 Phase 4: `whileM_`, `untilM_`, `forM_`, `replicateM_`
from `std/monad-control.ssc`.

[whileMOption, whileMList, untilMOption, untilMList, forMOption, forMList, replicateMOption, replicateMList, untilMResultOption, untilMResultEither, iterateWhileMOption, iterateWhileMEither](std/monad-control.ssc)

[Left, Right](std/either.ssc)

## whileMOption — count to 3

```scalascript
var i = 0
val r1 = whileMOption(
  () => Some(i < 3),
  () => { i = i + 1; Some(()) }
)
println(r1)
println(i)
```

## whileMOption — short-circuits on None

```scalascript
var j = 0
val r2 = whileMOption(
  () => if j < 2 then Some(true) else None,
  () => { j = j + 1; Some(()) }
)
println(r2)
println(j)
```

## untilMOption — loop until i reaches 5

```scalascript
var k = 0
val r3 = untilMOption(
  () => Some(k >= 5),
  () => { k = k + 1; Some(()) }
)
println(r3)
println(k)
```

## forMOption — sum via side-effecting traverse

```scalascript
var total = 0
val r4 = forMOption(List(1, 2, 3, 4), (x: Int) => { total = total + x; Some(()) })
println(r4)
println(total)
```

## forMOption — short-circuits on None

```scalascript
var count = 0
val r5 = forMOption(List(1, 2, 3), (x: Int) =>
  if x < 3 then { count = count + 1; Some(()) } else None
)
println(r5)
println(count)
```

## replicateMOption — run body 4 times

```scalascript
var n = 0
val r6 = replicateMOption(4, () => { n = n + 1; Some(()) })
println(r6)
println(n)
```

## forMOption inside direct[Option] block

```scalascript
val r7 = direct[Option] {
  a = Some(10)
  b = forMOption(List(1, 2, 3), (x: Int) => Some(()))
  Some(a + 100)
}
println(r7)
```

## forMList — collect side effects across branches

```scalascript
var listTotal = 0
val r8 = forMList(List(10, 20, 30), (x: Int) => { listTotal = listTotal + x; List(()) })
println(r8)
println(listTotal)
```

## untilMResultOption — do-while: body runs, then cond

```scalascript
var p = 0
val r9 = untilMResultOption(
  () => p >= 3,
  () => { p = p + 1; Some(p) }
)
println(r9)
println(p)
```

## untilMResultOption — short-circuits on None

```scalascript
var q = 0
val r10 = untilMResultOption(
  () => q >= 10,
  () => { q = q + 1; if q < 3 then Some(q) else None }
)
println(r10)
println(q)
```

## untilMResultOption — zero-iteration is impossible (do-while)

```scalascript
var s = 0
val r11 = untilMResultOption(
  () => true,
  () => { s = s + 1; Some(s * 10) }
)
println(r11)
println(s)
```

## untilMResultEither — short-circuits on Left

```scalascript
var t = 0
val r12 = untilMResultEither[String, Int](
  () => t >= 5,
  () => { t = t + 1; if t < 3 then Right(t) else Left("boom") }
)
println(r12)
println(t)
```

## iterateWhileMOption — step until cond becomes false

```scalascript
val r13 = iterateWhileMOption[Int](
  1,
  (n: Int) => Some(n * 2),
  (n: Int) => n < 100
)
println(r13)
```

## iterateWhileMOption — zero-iteration, returns init in pure

```scalascript
val r14 = iterateWhileMOption[Int](
  42,
  (n: Int) => Some(n + 1),
  (n: Int) => n < 0
)
println(r14)
```

## iterateWhileMEither — short-circuits on Left from step

```scalascript
val r15 = iterateWhileMEither[String, Int](
  1,
  (n: Int) => if n < 4 then Right(n + 1) else Left("stop at " + n),
  (n: Int) => n < 10
)
println(r15)
```
